.TH TB-COMPLETION 1 "December 2025" "ToolBox 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tb-completion \- generate shell completion script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tb completion
.I SHELL
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate shell completion scripts for ToolBox. Completion scripts enable tab-completion of commands and flags in your shell, making it faster and easier to use ToolBox.
.PP
The completion command supports:
.TP
.B bash
Bourne Again SHell
.TP
.B zsh
Z Shell
.TP
.B fish
Friendly Interactive SHell
.TP
.B powershell
PowerShell (Windows)
.SH BASH
To load completions in your current shell session:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
source <(tb completion bash)
.fi
.in
.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:
.PP
.B Linux:
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion bash | sudo tee /etc/bash_completion.d/tb
.fi
.in
.PP
.B macOS:
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion bash > $(brew --prefix)/etc/bash_completion.d/tb
.fi
.in
.PP
After installing, restart your shell or source your .bashrc:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
source ~/.bashrc
.fi
.in
.SH ZSH
To load completions in your current shell session:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
source <(tb completion zsh)
.fi
.in
.PP
To load completions for every new session, add to your ~/.zshrc:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
autoload -Uz compinit
compinit
tb completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_tb"
.fi
.in
.PP
After modifying ~/.zshrc, restart your shell or run:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
source ~/.zshrc
.fi
.in
.SH FISH
To load completions in your current shell session:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion fish | source
.fi
.in
.PP
To load completions for every new session:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/tb.fish
.fi
.in
.SH POWERSHELL
To load completions in your current shell session:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion powershell | Out-String | Invoke-Expression
.fi
.in
.PP
To load completions for every new session, add the output to your PowerShell profile:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
tb completion powershell >> $PROFILE
.fi
.in
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tb completion bash > /tmp/tb-completion.bash
Generate bash completion script and save to file
.TP
.B tb completion zsh | less
View generated zsh completion script
.TP
.B sudo tb completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/tb
Install bash completion system-wide (requires root)
.SH FEATURES
Shell completion provides:
.TP
\(bu
Command name completion (build, test, start, etc.)
.TP
\(bu
Flag completion (\-\-dry\-run, \-\-context, etc.)
.TP
\(bu
Context name completion for \-\-context flag
.TP
\(bu
Command descriptions displayed during completion
